cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with propositional dynamic logic and its extensions for message passing systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the synthesis problem for communicating finite-state machines. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with the construction of finite-state machines and the model checking problem. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the construction of communicating finite-state machines for message sequence charts. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the verification of properties in message passing systems.
